	<element id="ID_DMSG_WAY_OF_THE_FLORAL_SOUL_NATURES_BLESSING" source="Way of the Floral Soul" type="Archetype Feature" name="Nature's Blessing">
		<description>
			<p>When you choose this subclass at level 3, you learn a cantrip from the Druid spell list. Also, at level 5, you can cast plant growth once per day without paying the component cost. Any additional uses of this feature costs 4 ki points.</p>
		</description>
		</element>

	<element id="ID_DMSG_WAY_OF_THE_FLORAL_SOUL_BLOSSOM" source="Way of the Floral Soul" type="Archetype Feature" name="Blossom">
		<description>
			<p>Starting at the third level when you adopt this tradition you can manifest part of the nature within your own soul. By expending 1 Ki point and a bonus action you can take one of these forms for 1 minute:</p>
			<p class="indent"><strong><em>Aspect of the Lotus.</em></strong> You gain advantage on all Performance checks and you can cast the cantrip Shillelagh to empower your unarmed strikes. In addition you can use the ability <b>Dance of Petals:</b> you create a gentle rain of lotus petals that fall around you. On the first hit against a hostile creature on your turn you can force it to make a wisdom saving throw against your monk DC, on a failed save that creature will have disadvantage on the first attack it makes against you until the end of your next turn, you also can spend 1 Ki point to heal a creature within 10 feet of you for a amount equal to your martial arts die + your wisdom modifier. When you use your Flurry of Blows, you can replace one of the unarmed strikes with a use of this feature without spending a ki point for the healing.</p>
			<p class="indent"><strong><em>Aspect of the Rose.</em></strong> You gain an advantage on all Deception rolls. In addition you can use the ability <b>Rose's Thorn:</b> You create semi corporeal vines around your body, this vines can be extended up to 30 feet and use it unharmly on a creature or object to pull or grab them. Your attacks also gain an increased range of up to 10 feet, they deal Piercing instead of Bludgeoning damage and your martial arts die increases by 1 in damage class (becoming 1d6 if it's 1d4, etc). You can also use a bonus action to grab an object and move up to 30 feet.</p>
			<p class="indent"><strong><em>Aspect of the Orchid.</em></strong> You gain advantage on all Intimidation/Persuasion rolls depending on which orchid type you choose. In addition you can use the ability Floral Adaptation: as different kinds of orchids sprout from the surface of your body you can empower yourself depending on what you want in the moment. Choose one of orchid from the adaptation table below and gain resistance against its respective damage type you've bonded to, you also deal 1d4 of the chosen damage type on all melee weapon attacks and unarmed strikes, this damage rises to 1d6 at 6th level, 1d8 at 11th level, and 1d10 at 17th level.</p>
			<p><table>
				<thead>
					<tr><td class="col-20">Orchid Colours</td></tr>
				</thead>
				<tr><td>1 Brown</td><td>6 Black</td></tr>
				<tr><td>2 White</td><td>7 White+Purple</td></tr>
				<tr><td>3 Orange</td><td>8 Purple</td></tr>
				<tr><td>4 Blue+Black</td><td>9 Pink</td></tr>
				<tr><td>5 Light Blue</td><td>10 Dark Blue</td></tr>
			</table></p>
		</description>
	</element>


